synopsis:
The Art & Compromise series, conceived by Beaconsfield in collaboration with City & Guilds of London Art School, addresses the various forms and occasions when compromise might enter into art practice.
The 20th century concept of the artist as a politically alienated idealist has undergone significant shifts in recent years. Is there any form of moral obligation still within art’s purpose? What price integrity? Can the negotiations of compromise be catalysts for creative invention?&#8232;&#8232;

Jon Thompson will participate in the fourth in the Art & Compromise Series at 2pm on 18th February 2010 at Beaconsfield.&#8232;&#8232;
